# Error Handling Guidelines

## Strict Client/Server Error Separation

**This SDK has a strict separation between client-side and server-side errors:**

- **Client Errors** (`@/utils/errors-client`): Used in client code (RPC client, API wrappers, tool helpers, etc.)
- **Server Errors** (`@/utils/errors-server`): Used in server code (Bare worker, RPC handlers, model operations, etc.)

This separation ensures:
1. Clear boundaries between client and server responsibilities
2. Proper error handling across the RPC boundary
3. Consistent error codes within each domain

## Use Structured Error Classes

**ALWAYS use the structured error classes** from the appropriate location instead of plain `Error`:

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER do this
throw new Error("Model not found");
throw new Error(`Failed to load model: ${modelId}`);

// ✅ ALWAYS do this - Client code
import { InvalidResponseError } from "@/utils/errors-client";
throw new InvalidResponseError("loadModel");

// ✅ ALWAYS do this - Server code
import { ModelNotFoundError, ModelLoadFailedError } from "@/utils/errors-server";
throw new ModelNotFoundError(modelId);
throw new ModelLoadFailedError(details);
```

## Error Class Naming Convention

All error classes:
- End with `Error` suffix (e.g., `ModelNotFoundError`)
- Extend `QvacErrorBase` from `@qvac/error`
- Are defined in:
  - **Client errors**: `/utils/errors-client.ts` (codes 50,001-52,000)
  - **Server errors**: `/utils/errors-server.ts` (codes 52,001-54,000)
- Public API errors are exported from the main `index.ts`

## Error Chaining - Preserve Original Errors

**ALWAYS preserve the original error** using the `cause` parameter when catching and re-throwing:

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER lose the original error
try {
  await fs.readdir(modelDir);
} catch (error) {
  throw new ModelFileLocateFailedError(modelType, modelPath);
}

// ✅ ALWAYS preserve the original error
try {
  await fs.readdir(modelDir);
} catch (error) {
  throw new ModelFileLocateFailedError(modelType, modelPath, error);
  // The original error is accessible via .cause property
}
```

## Error Constructor Patterns

### Simple Errors (no details)
```typescript
throw new InvalidOperationError();
throw new StreamEndedError();
```

### Errors with Context
```typescript
throw new ModelNotFoundError(modelId);
throw new InvalidResponseError("embed");
throw new HTTPError(status, statusText);
```

### Errors with Details and Cause
```typescript
throw new ModelLoadFailedError(details, cause);
throw new EmbedFailedError(response.error, cause);
```

